div.p:
Prithee Reader observe Master Dels reasoning in this place is neither Logicall nor Theologicall;
                  Animadvers.
                this is the force of what he writes. The Prelates desired their government to bee confirmed by Kings to be Iure Divino; therefore the Assembly (for I know not else who he should meane by that tearme which hee useth ironically, the sacred Clergy) who desire the Parliament to settle their moddell of Church government and confirme it by civill sanction, is not Iure Divino.
